<Content>Ab Skipper is really good We have just returned from a 5 night stay at the Ab Skipper( july30-aug 4th) and we really enjoyed our stay here.The rooms are comfortable and spacious . The bathrooms was also big with good supply of nice toiletiries . As the Hotel is very new , the bath towels are lovely and fluffy! The rooms are cleaned very well and do have free internet , however the wifi works in frequently but you can get a wired connection. For a city hotel , the 2 swimming pools are an added bliss. The Breakfast food quality is very good and the service is pleasant. The location is near the Port olympic area , which is a short (10 mins) walk to the city centre. The beach is only a 50m walk. Being vegetarians , we were surprised at the number of really good vegetarians restaurants. For pizza, La veronica is unbeatable and is located at 2-4 Rambla del Raval. Also La Bascula at 30 C. dels Flassaders is good for crepes, pastas,sandwiches ,fresh juices etc. Juicy Jones at 76 c.Hospital is good for freshly squeezed juices, lovely salads , sandwiches and is inexpensive., Amaltea at 164 Diptacio is another good veggie restaurant. So is Buenas Migas at 6 Placa Bonsucces. 
