<Content>Nice Hotel We stayed in this hotel from 20 to 23 July and found it to be very good. The location (Port Olympic) is slightly out of the way, but it is only a 10-15 minute walk into the city. If you are looking for a hotel in central Barcelona then this is not for you - but it is certainly close enough to walk everywhere and it has the advantage of being vey close to the beach with amazing views of the Med. The hotel is very new and so the facilities are very good - the rooms are well appointed and the pool areas (there are 2, one on the roof of the hotel and one at ground level) are superb for a non-resort hotel. The staff were efficient (both on the desk and in the bar and restaurant), although not overly friendly. We found the food to be very good and the cocktails at the bars were great.Overall, I would not hesitate to stay again and would recommend this hotel. 
