<Content>Service poor for a 5 star!! I wanted to take my wife for a long weekend away to Barcelona and had planned to stay at The Arts but it was full.I then heard that the Skipper was a good alternative and booked for our 5 night trip.Generally this hotel gives a good standard of quality but with a few rather large annoying problems listed below.1) The key card to our room did not recognise the lock every time we tried to get in the room. We would then had to go to reception to replace the key and there attitude about the problem was rather poor and quite rude on occassion trying to blame it on us putting it in wrong! You dont expect that from a 5 star.2) The hotel is located near the hospital. There was numerous occassions that ambulance sirens would go off during the day and night which were quite annoying.3) Our stay was over a weekend. We had a lovely room overlooking the pool and sea but obviously being the weekend the hotel was quite busy with drunken revalers drinking at the outside bar til gone 4.30 one morning!! It was quite noisy and difficult to get to sleep.On a good note the rooms were spacious and the bathrooms appointed very well. I agree with some of the other reviews about the shower leaking but to be fair its not that bad.Breakfast was one of the best buffets that we have had in a hotel but at 23 euros you would hope it would be.Would i stay here again? Only if i couldnt get in to the ARTs.Please Please can the staff have some more training on how to act in a 5 star hotel rather that a 4 star. 
