<Content>Moderate Hotel My husband and I stayed in the AB Skipper hotel for one weekend in June. He had a conference at the Arts Hotel and we originally wanted to continue to stay there but they had no availability. The AB Skipper is a moderate hotel. For a 5 star hotel, it is quite disappointing. Our rooms were serviced only once a day (usually the housekeeping comes again in the evening but not at this hotel). Also, they have wireless internet and we were quite impressed by this when we first were told this. However, the internet only works if you are in certain areas of the room. So we ended up having to sit in the corner of the bed to have internet access. Very strange! Also, at night, the lobby has these incredibly bright ceiling lights - which totally take all the potential ambiance away. Overall, the AB Skipper was moderate, to say the least. If you're looking for a hotel that is right near the beach and that is not too expensive, this is the one for you. But otherwise, if you have higher expectations for a 5 star hotel, stay at Hotel Arts! 
