<Content>Good location near Beach and marina This is a newly built hotel in Barcelona near the Marina and beach area. The rooms are fabulous and the bathrooms very spacious with separate bath and shower, however we had problems with the temperature of the water being too cold. We complained but it took them nearly another 12 hours to fix it, the tap with the thermostat needed to be replaced. The hotel did not offer anything extra to us due to this problems which for a 5* very much annoyed me, as we were only there for 3 days. The two swimming pools are fabulous, one is on the roof overlooking the beach. One of the porter was most friendly to us - he spoke to the maintenance person in English regarding the water. Location is good and metro is just across the road, to walk along the beach and marina is very closeby and also the casino is around the corner, near all the lovely restaurants. Breakfast was included in our deal, but when we were checking out they tried to charged us, we had to ask for the manager and nearly missed our bus to the airport. All in all it is a good hotel - but I suppose it has teething problems being new, however they should look after their visitors better if they want more to come back! 
