<Content>Excellent hotel by the sea We have just returned from a weekend at this new hotel in the Villa Olympica area of Barcelona. Everything was excellent from the moment we checked in. We had a room on the 6th floor with a balcony and sea view, the room and bathroom were immaculate. Robes and slippers are provided, the towels are huge and fluffy, the toiletries are Loewe, there is a professional hairdryer, a walk in shower with a rain showerhead. The room itself has a flat screen tv and dvd player, tea and coffeee making facilities, and the closets have internal lights that come on when the doors are opened.The pools are now both in use, we used the rooftop pool, a lovely place to be with views over the city.Only one problem, if you are a light sleeper and do not wear ear plugs, there are continually sirens sounding through the night, I had very little sleep as everytime I went to sleep it was to be awoken by these sirens( from ambulances, hospital nearby)that aside, no negative comments whatsoever. 
